<br>
BTW, I had the search settings setup to show only the rings I was interested in (rings, hp).  It wasn't a confusion on the item or name.  I remembered it precisely because you're always harping on how pricing is so unfair to poor potters.  Perhaps it's because you have a natural bent to charge 3x the going rates and find it frustrating when that doesn't work.<br>
<br>
There's nothing wrong with charging high, I do it myself when I don't care how soon things sell.  But, it gets real old hearing people whine about it, though.  If you aren't making enough plat from your trade, do something else.  Tradeskill proffits always go down. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/15/02 3:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=66>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It was you, Jar</span><hr size=1> Bjond... I've never sold those rings.  I only recently bought one, it's the only one I've ever had, and I wear it.  After you said that I took my ring and put it in trader mode to see if I'd already had an assigned cost... I didn't.  Never sold that ring before in my life.  So get your facts straight.  There's a few folks with names like Jakrall and such, maybe one of them wanted that price, but again, I'm not a Jewelcrafter.  I know exactly how my rings went... I had two 6 dex 6 str rings I bought from Coriolis for about 400 pp.  I upgraded one to a coldain ring and sold it before the new bazaar.  Then I bought a 6/65 ring and sold the other 6 dex 6 str in the bazaar for what Coriolis charged me to make it.  That's my current set up.  So check your facts.<br>
<br>
And I'm not harping on unfair prices to potters... I'm harping on people who say some arbitrary mark up (usually 50% to 100%) is always appropriate in tradeskills and they're getting ripped off if they don't get that exact amount, dispite the fact that they sure don't complain when the mark up is 10% or less!  And I'll defend any tradeskill, regardless of wether or not I'm in it, because it's an alternative way of playing the game... some fight monsters for exp, leveling up till they can kill bigger monsters.  Some, however, can make items for money, using that money to level up their skill till they can make better items.  This is why it really hurts to see massive price cuts and such... imagine seeing you're suddenly getting 50% less exp per mob when you fight.  <br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel<br>
